The advantage of our study is to quantify relationships not only between similar emotions but also between dissimilar emotions that are linked to each other associatively or by cooccurence. We examined the relevance between the most fundamental mutually exclusive emotional concepts: “GOOD” and “BAD.” The result in Fig. 4 shows that “GOOD” and “BAD” were mutually connected by an edge whose weight is \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
